## Style guide

- TechCrunch register: short paragraphs, direct lede, funding-amount in first sentence for funding articles, quotes from CEO/CTO in paragraph 2-3, competitive context in paragraph 4-5, brief background on the company near the end.
- Byline will be added separately — do not include a byline.
- Do NOT include the word "TechCrunch" in the body.
- Use real peer company names naturally (CoreWeave, Lambda, Runpod, etc.) — these are real companies.
- Dollar amounts written as "$35 million" in prose.
- Do NOT add a "Disclosure" or "Related reading" section.
- Do NOT reference this being a fictional or generated article.

## Output format

Return ONLY the article body in markdown. No JSON wrapping. No metadata. Start with the first paragraph of the article (the lede).
